    "We do not think so.",
    "Inspired by Krueger and Osler (2022), we argue that affective artificial agents enjoy only a thin form of agency, as opposed to the thick form of agency humans enjoy.",
    "This characterization aims to capture three macroscopic differences.",
    "12 The first one concerns experience.",
    "Humans experience a rich world of valenced objects and events, means and ends, joys and sorrows."
